# Why Storage Matters

Container restarts **wipe the writable layer.**

- Image's read-only layers **stay** (cached on node).
- Writable top layer **deleted** on container removal.

> By design — cattle, not pets. But `/var/lib/postgres`, `/data`, uploads, caches — **all gone on restart.**

## Two lifetimes

- **Pod-lifetime** — a volume as long as the **Pod**: `emptyDir`, ConfigMap/Secret. Scratch, IPC, config.
- **Cluster-lifetime** — **external** (cloud disk, NFS) surviving Pod + node death + reschedule. **PV / PVC**.

## The question per workload

> **How long should this data live?** → picks the volume type.

*Pods are ephemeral, so durable state lives in a separate resource the Pod mounts.*
